# 🧠 Big Data & Cloud Computing Project  
## Yelp Reviews Sentiment Analysis using AWS (S3, Glue, Athena, EMR, QuickSight)

---

## 📌 Project Overview

This project demonstrates an end-to-end **Big Data analytics pipeline** on the Yelp Academic Dataset using **Amazon Web Services (AWS)**. The system processes large-scale review data (≈ 6.99 million reviews, ~5GB JSON) and performs **data ingestion, transformation, NLP processing, sentiment analysis, machine learning, and visualization**.

The pipeline is fully cloud-based and scalable using AWS services such as:

- Amazon S3 (Data Lake Storage)
- AWS Glue (Metadata Catalog)
- Amazon Athena (Serverless SQL Queries)
- Amazon EMR Serverless (Apache Spark Processing)
- Spark MLlib (Machine Learning)
- Amazon QuickSight (Dashboards)
- IAM + CloudWatch (Security & Monitoring)

---

## 📊 Dataset

- **Dataset Name:** Yelp Academic Reviews Dataset  
- **Source:** https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/yelp-dataset/yelp-dataset  
- **Size:** ~5GB  
- **Records:** ~6.99 million reviews  
- **Format:** JSON  

The dataset contains:
- Review text (unstructured data)
- Ratings (1–5 stars)
- User IDs, Business IDs
- Useful, funny, and cool vote counts
- Date of review

---

## 🏗️ Architecture Overview

The system follows a cloud-native big data pipeline:

1. Data ingestion into **Amazon S3**
2. Schema discovery using **AWS Glue Crawler**
3. Data querying using **Amazon Athena**
4. Distributed processing using **Amazon EMR Serverless (Spark)**
5. NLP preprocessing and sentiment classification
6. Machine Learning using **Logistic Regression (Spark MLlib)**
7. Visualization using **Amazon QuickSight**

